# Sababich Dashboard System

## Overview

This project includes a therapist-facing analytics dashboard built for the Sababich game.

Important:  
The dashboard architecture and implementation were designed and developed with the assistance of Claude (AI), based on detailed requirements and iterative refinement.

The system enables tracking, storing, and presenting player performance data across multiple sessions, focusing strictly on raw measurable metrics without any clinical interpretation.

---

## What the System Does

After gameplay sessions, the system:

- Collects gameplay metrics per level
- Aggregates them into a session record
- Stores session history (local + cloud backup)
- Updates a static dashboard HTML file
- Allows therapists to view data via a fixed link or button

---

## Project Structure

### Backend (Unity - C#)

Assets/Scripts/Outputs_to_Cloud/

- SessionIdentity.cs — stores current player identity
- SessionRecord.cs — data model for sessions
- SessionDataCollector.cs — builds session data
- CloudSessionHistory.cs — manages cloud session history
- SessionExporter.cs — generates dashboard HTML with embedded data
- ViewDashboardButton.cs — opens dashboard manually

---

### Frontend (Dashboard)

Assets/StreamingAssets/Dashboard/

- sababich_dashboard.html — main dashboard file
- dashboard.css — styling
- dashboard.js — filtering, sorting, charts, notes

---

## Data Tracked

### Raw Metrics (from game)

- Passed / Failed per level
- Coins per level
- Time to target
- Total served dishes
- Perfect served dishes
- Duplicate ingredient clicks
- Gluten-sensitive child appeared
- Gluten-sensitive child served by mistake

### Derived Metrics (calculated)

- Incorrect dishes
- Gluten child handled correctly
- Average dish preparation time

---

## Session History

- Each gameplay session is stored separately
- Sessions are linked to a specific player
- No overwriting of previous data
- Stored locally (primary) and in Unity Cloud Save (backup)

---

## Dashboard Access

The dashboard is:

- Not opened automatically
- Accessed via a button in MainMenu
- Stored locally at:

Application.persistentDataPath/Dashboard/sababich_dashboard.html

- No server required
- No terminal commands required
- Works offline

---

## Therapist-Oriented Design

The dashboard:

- Displays raw data only
- Does not perform analysis or diagnosis
- Groups metrics into neutral sections:
  - Dishes Served
  - Attention & Repetition
  - Rule-Based Responses
  - Level Outcome

Includes:

- Filtering (player, date, level, etc.)
- Sorting (coins, errors, time, etc.)
- Session history
- Therapist notes (stored in localStorage)

---

## Final Setup (Unity Editor)

1. Open MainMenu scene  
2. Create UI Button  
3. Attach ViewDashboardButton component  
4. In OnClick() assign:

ViewDashboardButton.OpenDashboard()

